						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone built into the wall of the Kalamēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1248.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1171, Kīlaka, Chaitra, ba. 3, Sunday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1248, March 14,</hi> the weekday being Saturday and Śaka year current.</p>						

						<p>The inscription records the death of an individual (name lost), in a fight against Jōyidēva of <hi rend="bold">Gutoḷalu</hi> at the instance of Chaṭṭayadēva of <hi rend="bold">Halasige-nāḍu,</hi> during a cattle-raid. It mentions the One Thousand of <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kuṁdugoḷa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
